The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, August 13, 2003 				 2.7% growth in first quarter
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Bangalore, Aug. 12: Cellular subscribers grew by 2.75 per cent in the first quarter of 2003-04, while mobile subscribers, including limited mobility users, grew by 4.8 per cent. 																								The Telecom Regulatory Authority of India (Trai) today released data regarding the growth of cellular, limited mobility and internet subscribers in April-June 2003.																								According to the release, cellular operators added 36 lakh subscribers in April-July 2003 compared with around 13.0 lakh subscribers during the same period last year, showing a growth of over 2.75 times.																								The cellular and limited mobility additions registered a combined growth of 67 lakh in April-July 2003 as compared with 14 lakh during the same period in the previous year. 
